    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but those \"small moments\" feel like such a distraction, don't they? like putting a band-aid on a void. if the fundamental reality is that everything eventually decays and turns to dust, then any meaning we manufacture is just a lie we tell ourselves to stay sane. it feels more honest to just admit that the struggle is unnecessary. if there's no ultimate point, why is there this constant pressure to just keep performing the act of living?",
